12.body: Notes The notation Vx or Vy refers to any general-purpose register (i.e. registers 0 through F). The notation for other registers is as follows: I - memory address register PC - program counter register SP - stack pointer register DT - delay timer register ST - sound timer register. Additionally, nnn refers to some memory address, and kk refers to some constant byte value. Many instructions have multiple versions. The format and semantics (in both English and C-style pseudocode) of each are listed.
12.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » Appendix A: CHIP-8 Instruction Reference
12.title: Appendix A: CHIP-8 Instruction Reference

13.body: 7xkk - ADD Vx, kk : Adds the byte kk to the value in Vx . The result is stored in Vx . Vx = Vx + kk; 8xy4 - ADD Vx, Vy : Adds the value in Vy to the value in Vx . The result is stored in Vx ; Vy is unaffected. Vx = Vx + Vy; Fx1E : Adds the value in Vx to memory address register I. The result is stored in I; Vx is unaffected. I = I + Vx;
13.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » ADD - Addition
13.title: ADD - Addition

14.body: 8xy2 - AND Vx, Vy : Performs a bitwise AND of the values in Vx and Vy . The result is stored in Vx ; Vy is unaffected. Vx = Vx & Vy;
14.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » AND - Bitwise AND
14.title: AND - Bitwise AND

15.body: Fx33 - BCD Vx : Stores the digits of the decimal representation of the value in Vx into three memory locations starting at the address in I. *I = hundreds_digit(Vx); *(I+1) = tens_digit(Vx); *(I+2) = ones_digit(Vx);
15.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » BCD - Binary-coded decimal
15.title: BCD - Binary-coded decimal

16.body: 2nnn - CALL nnn : Pushes the current value of PC onto the top of the stack, and sets PC to nnn . SP = SP + 1; stack[SP] = PC; PC = nnn;
16.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » CALL - Call subroutinue
16.title: CALL - Call subroutinue

17.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » CLS - Clear screen
17.title: CLS - Clear screen

18.body: Dxyn - DRW Vx, Vy, n : Draws the n byte sprite located at the address in I on the screen, at coordinates ( Vx , Vy ). Drawing is done using XOR, and VF is set if any pixels are cleared in the process. Drawing is also done in a wrap-around fashion, so any part of the sprite that would be placed outside of the display boundaries is drawn on the opposite side. draw_sprite(Vx, Vy, I, n);
18.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » DRW - Draw sprite
18.title: DRW - Draw sprite

19.body: 1nnn - JP nnn : Sets PC to the address nnn . PC = nnn; Bnnn - JP V0, nnn : Sets PC to the sum of the value in V0 and nnn . PC = V0 + nnn;
19.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » JP - Jump
19.title: JP - Jump

2.title: Binary and Hexadecimal Numbers

20.body: 6xkk - LD Vx, kk : Loads the byte value kk into Vx . Vx = kk; 8xy0 - LD Vx, Vy : Loads the value in Vy into Vx . Vy is unaffected. Vx = Vy; Annn - LD I, nnn : Loads the address nnn into I. I = nnn; Fx07 - LD Vx, DT : Loads the value of DT into Vx . The value of the delay timer is unaffected. Vx = DT; Fx0A - LD Vx, K : Loads the value of the next pressed key into Vx . Program execution is halted until a key is pressed. Vx = get_next_key(); Fx15 - LD DT, Vx : Loads the value in Vx into DT. Vx is unaffected. DT = Vx; Fx18 - LD ST, Vx : Loads the value in Vx into ST. Vx is unaffected. ST = Vx; Fx55 - LD I, Vx : Loads the registers V0 through Vx into the memory locations starting at the address in I. All registers are unaffected. *I = V0; *(I+1) = V1; ...; *(I+x) = Vx; Fx65 - LD Vx, I : Loads the values in memory starting at the address in I into registers V0 through Vx . All memory locations are unaffected. V0 = I[0]; V1 = I[1]; ...; Vx = I[x];
20.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » LD - Load
20.title: LD - Load

21.body: Fx29 - LDF Vx : Loads the location of the hexadecimal sprite corresponding to the value in Vx into I. I = hex_sprites[Vx];
21.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » LDF - Load font
21.title: LDF - Load font

22.body: 8xy1 - OR Vx, Vy : Performs a bitwise OR of the values in Vx and Vy . The result is stored in Vx ; Vy is unaffected. Vx = Vx | Vy;
22.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » OR - Bitwise OR
22.title: OR - Bitwise OR

23.body: 00EE - RET : Removes and sets the program counter to the top-most address on the stack. PC = stack[SP]; SP = SP - 1;
23.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » RET - Return from subroutinue
23.title: RET - Return from subroutinue

24.body: Cxkk - RND Vx, kk : Generates a random byte, then performs a bitwise AND between it and kk . The result is stored in Vx . Vx = rnd() & kk;
24.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » RND - Random value
24.title: RND - Random value

25.body: 3xkk - SE Vx, kk : Skips the next instruction if Vx has the value kk . PC = (Vx == kk ? (PC + 2) : (PC + 1)); 4xkk - SNE Vx, kk : Skips the next instruction if Vx does not have the value kk . PC = (Vx != kk ? (PC + 2) : (PC + 1)); 5xy0 - SE Vx, Vy : Skips the next instruction if Vx and Vy have the same values. PC = (Vx == Vy ? (PC + 2) : (PC + 1)); 9xy0 - SNE Vx, Vy : Skips the next instruction if Vx and Vy do not have the same values. PC = (Vx != Vy ? (PC + 2) : (PC + 1)); Ex9E - SKP Vx : Skips the next instruction if the key with the same value as Vx is pressed. PC = (key_pressed(Vx) ? (PC + 2) : (PC + 1)); ExA1 - SKNP Vx : Skips the next instruction if the key with the same value as Vx is not pressed. PC = (!key_pressed(Vx) ? (PC + 2) : (PC + 1));
25.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » S - Skip next instruction
25.title: S - Skip next instruction

26.body: 8xy6 - SHR Vx : Sets VF to the value of the least significant bit of the value in Vx, then shifts the value in Vx right by one bit. The result is stored in Vx . VF = Vx & 1; Vx = Vx >> 1; 8xyE - SHL Vx : Sets VF to the value of the most significant bit of the value in Vx, then shifts the value in Vx left by one bit. The result is stored in Vx . VF = msb(Vx); Vx = Vx << 1;
26.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » SH - Bitwise shift
26.title: SH - Bitwise shift

27.body: 8xy5 - SUB Vx, Vy : Subtracts the value in Vy from the value in Vx . The result is stored in Vx ; Vy is unaffected. If the result would be negative, VF is set to 1; otherwise, it is set to 0. Vx = Vx - Vy; 8xy7 - SUBN Vx, Vy : Subtracts the value in Vx from the value in Vy . The result is stored in Vx ; Vy is unaffected. If the result would be negative, VF is set to 1; otherwise, it is set to 0. Vx = Vy - Vx;
27.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » SUB - Subtraction
27.title: SUB - Subtraction

28.body: 0nnn - SYS nnn : Jumps to machine code subroutinue at address nnn . This instruction is deprecated, and ignored by most modern emulators. PC = nnn;
28.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » SYS - System call [DEPRECATED]
28.title: SYS - System call [DEPRECATED]

29.body: 8xy3 - XOR Vx, Vy : Performs a bitwise exclusive OR (XOR) of the values in Vx and Vy . The result is stored in Vx ; Vy is unaffected. Vx = Vx ^ Vy;
29.breadcrumbs: Appendicies » Full CHIP-8 Instruction Set » XOR - Bitwise XOR
29.title: XOR - Bitwise XOR
